<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,908,2015]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,908,935]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
The combination of mesoscutum with pale-orange hairs, mesepisternum with imbricate insterspaces, and T2–T5 covered with sparse black short setae is sufficient to diagnose 
<taxonomicName authority="Ferrari, 2019" authorityName="Ferrari" authorityYear="2019" box="[987,1130,945,971]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferenudus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[987,1006,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1021,1130,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">ferenudus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1138,1201,945,971]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1138,1201,945,971]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
This species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1956" box="[264,350,981,1007]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kerri">
<emphasis box="[264,350,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">C. kerri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as in their females (the male of 
<taxonomicName authority="Ferrari, 2019" authorityName="Ferrari" authorityYear="2019" box="[709,850,981,1007]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferenudus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[709,850,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">C. ferenudus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[858,920,981,1007]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[858,920,981,1007]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is unknown) the mesoscutum has pale-orange hairs and T2–T5 are not covered with dense appressed hairs. However, the two species can be distinguished from one another by clypeus striate only below in 
<taxonomicName authority="Ferrari, 2019" authorityName="Ferrari" authorityYear="2019" box="[654,796,1053,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferenudus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[654,796,1053,1079]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">C. ferenudus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[804,867,1053,1079]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[804,867,1053,1079]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(clypeus striate throughout in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1956" box="[1210,1297,1053,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kerri">
<emphasis box="[1210,1297,1053,1079]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">C. kerri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); and mesepisternum with imbricate interspaces in 
<taxonomicName authority="Ferrari, 2019" authorityName="Ferrari" authorityYear="2019" box="[600,742,1089,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferenudus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[600,742,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">C. ferenudus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[749,812,1089,1115]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[749,812,1089,1115]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(mesepisternum with smooth interspaces in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1956" box="[1311,1398,1089,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kerri">
<emphasis box="[1311,1398,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">C. kerri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
